  , issueBody =
      Just
        "RethinkDB's Java driver blocks forever (or at least that is the symptom) if the RethinkDB database connection dies - e.g. because the database is shut down, or because an intermediate firewall or load balancer (e.g. AWS's load balancer) kills the TCP connection.\r\n\r\nIf I run the following code with a local rethink DB database, then shut the rethinkDB database down, the application will block indefinitely when it runs the next rethinkDB command (either insert or query).\r\n\r\n\tpackage rethink_connectivity_test;\r\n\t\r\n\timport com.rethinkdb.RethinkDB;\r\n\timport com.rethinkdb.net.Connection;\r\n\t\r\n\tpublic class ConnectivityTest {\r\n\t\r\n\t\tpublic static void main(String [] args) throws Exception {\r\n\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\tRethinkDB r = RethinkDB.r;\r\n\t\t\tConnection c = r.connection()\r\n\t\t\t\t    .hostname(\"localhost\")\r\n\t\t\t\t    .port(28015)\r\n\t\t\t\t    .connect();\r\n\t\t\tr.db(\"test\").tableCreate(\"bucket\").run(c);\r\n\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\tint counter = 0;\r\n\t\t\twhile(true) { \r\n\t\t\t\tr.db(\"test\").table(\"bucket\").insert(r.hashMap(\"counter\", counter)).run(c);\r\n\t\t\t\tlong total = r.db(\"test\").table(\"bucket\").count().run(c);\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\tSystem.out.println(\"Document count is \" + total);\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\tThread.sleep(1000);\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n\t\r\nI would anticipate that the application code could in some way be informed and handle this scenario."
